net.sourceforge.waters.model.expr

Interface Operator

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    BinaryOperator, BooleanOperator, BuiltInFunction, UnaryOperator

    public interface Operator

    The common interface for unary and binary operators.

    Operators are used by parsers and scanners in situations where expressions need to be created from operator names, before the class of the expression is known. The can be looked up in the operator table (OperatorTable) by their name and contain information such as the binding priority of operators and instructions how to construct the actual expression.

    Author:
    Robi Malik
